Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into
½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1} into ½-inch pieces
(use the rest as you like). Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into
½-inch pieces. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes, diced onion, and green pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Spread out across entire sheet. Roast on top rack until golden
brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @bacon{4%ounce} in a dry, large pan over medium-high heat. Cook,
turning occasionally, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
paper-towel-lined plate. Discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat (you'll use it
to cook the eggs).

> TIP: Lower heat if bacon begins to brown too quickly.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @bibigo GOTCHU Korean Hot Sauce{1} and
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Set aside.

Return pan with bacon fat to medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and
cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered
off heat until ready to serve.

Once veggies have 3-5 minutes left, remove from oven. Halve @potato buns{2} and
place, cut sides up, on same baking sheet. Sprinkle top buns with
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/2%cup}. Return to oven until bread is toasted, cheese is
melted, and veggies are tender.

Spread cut sides of bottom buns with a bit of bibigo GOTCHU mayo; fill buns with
bacon and eggs. Toss veggies with cilantro. Divide veggies and sandwiches
between plates. Serve with remaining bibigo GOTCHU mayo on the side.